properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 7 at 3:19AM CST until January 8 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...A PERIOD OF LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL DEVELOP THIS EVENING AND
CONTINUE INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING...

.Colder air will filter into the region today behind a cold front
that will pass through the Northland. This cold air will help
support some lake effect snow showers over the higher terrain of
Iron county in northwest Wisconsin, beginning this evening,
persisting into Wednesday morning. This snow could impact the
Wednesday morning commute for the Kimball, Montreal, Gile, and
Hurley areas.

* WHAT...Lake effect snow expected. Total snow accumulations of
between 2 to 4 inches will be possible.

* WHERE...Iron County.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 8 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Wednesday morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 8 AM CST WEDNESDAY
